name: Richard Jurasek
review: very overpriced food  cool to walk around but there are better places to eat and explore in sokcho  go to sokcho beach and the other port instead  the bridge was neat to walk on though

name: Nava K
review: basically  a market and seafood market  perhaps like one of those you may have visited in japan or elsewhere  of course  the fresh catch from the sea cannot be faulted and you also get to buy other stuffs as well  walk from one end to the other until you are satisfied  while also considering spending you money on the things which may lure your attention  for me personally  i thought a waste of my time

name: Nordiana Mat Salleh
review: many variety of seafood fries over here and also the live one and big lobster  nice experience to be here

name: Jinman Ha
review: quite mordern and regacy market are be in same place

name: Hong Gyu Park
review: you must try if you want to eat something all kinds of sea food and snack in daepo harbour korea

name: Andy Koh Woon Chieh
review: fresh seafood and quite empty during weekdays  good place to experience raw seafood

name: jaja na
review: so many seafood that gonna make you excited

name: Steve Choe
review: a must place to visit   great market place with variety of korean traditional cuisine

name: AiMei Huang
review: arrived there at night   a must try fried seafood and sweet potato

name: Karen Laurico
review: it s one of the best fish market i ve visited so far here in south korea  the atmosphere is so good since it is facing the pacific ocean and the view is amazing  it is also clean and organized  it offers variety of seafood products and other food products  we also enjoyed the cafe nearby

name: Chunghee Roh
review: no special things  many of markets open waiting for customers but can t find any specialty at each market  completely the same  also  the price is 30  up comparing to the same restaurant in downtown which is 3 km away from here  if you persue some moods  you can eat but if you are there with limited budget  go and find it in downtown  concerned about quality  downtown giving you high as well

name: INKYU PARK
review: 20 25 years ago  i had a good memory of daepohang fish market  but the facilities are better now than in the past  now all shops and facilities are mordernized  so i didn t feel the old memory now

name: Brandon
review: daepo port was so nice to look around  it was clean and tidy  the east sea is right in front of the port  a fresh raw fish was tasty  too

name: Valerie Ng
review: if you come here  be prepared for a very  fishy  smell because it s all seafood products  it was quite cold during winter and i m not a seafood fan so there is nothing for me here

name: Dinuka Adasooriya
review: we visit there at evening  nice place to have fried sea food  buy fish and other raw sea foods  there is a beautiful carriage rides around the harbour at night

name: Josh Vinno
review: just imagine you can buy seafood fresh from the sea

name: jang kenny kh
review: if u like to taste hoe  sashimi  raw fush mustle   u have many choices here  every resto serves it

name: Duyan Bukid
review: great place to eat super fresh king crab and beautiful lobster   will definitely visit again

name: Gene Lee
review: it was cheaper and nice before but now everything is expensive especially the

name: ARUNz

name: TB Foo

name: Allen Chang
review: fresh seafood all around and great to see all types of fresh live sea food

name: Kevin Kyeong-il Choi
review: very good  nice food  good ambience

name: Chris Tan

name: Ken Loh

name: Jasmin Schmidt
review: fresh seafood  they prepare what you have bought

name: Garry Chua
